r $1 worth of Luna. If Luna trades at $0.10, then one Terra will get you 10=
 Luna. If Luna trades at $20, then one Terra will get you 0.05 Luna. Doesn&=
#8217;t matter. The price of Luna is arbitrary, but one Terra always gets y=
ou $1 worth of Luna. (And vice versa: People can always exchange $1 worth o=
f Luna for one Terra.)</em></p></li><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 4px; margin=
-left: 8px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 4px;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><em>You s=
